        "id": "070b93a2ace8ffb4",
        "text": "Theory and application both benefit when they are linked.  Without an applied focus, it is easy for theory to lose focus, and to address easy problems rather than hard problems that demand greater complexity.  Application without theory can also lose shape and become a disorganized collection of practices.  If our perspective on expertise is to develop, it must have value in shaping practice."
